  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4130546543" />
    <a title="George" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10168276-george"><img alt="George" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1511867378p2/10168276.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4130546543?book_show_action=true">Jul 24, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="George" class="user" itemprop="url" name="George" href="/user/show/10168276-george">George</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10168276-george?shelf=1001-books-list-read-2006">1001-books-list-read-2006</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4130546543" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12371236952388344909">A very engaging, eventful, easy to read novel about Nashe. Nashe was a Boston City fire fighter for seven years. His wife left him and his young infant. Nashe takes the child to live with his sister. Nashe and his sister out of the blue each receive $200,000 dollars inheritance from their father who they have not seen for thirty years. Nashe quits his job. He buys a brand new Saab and spends a year driving around the USA. He picks up a battered Jack Pozzi, a full time poker card player. Together</span>
  <span id="freeText12371236952388344909" style="display:none">A very engaging, eventful, easy to read novel about Nashe. Nashe was a Boston City fire fighter for seven years. His wife left him and his young infant. Nashe takes the child to live with his sister. Nashe and his sister out of the blue each receive $200,000 dollars inheritance from their father who they have not seen for thirty years. Nashe quits his job. He buys a brand new Saab and spends a year driving around the USA. He picks up a battered Jack Pozzi, a full time poker card player. Together they go to a vast estate where two very rich retired guys, Flower and Stone, live. Pozzi has organised to play with Flower and Stone, expecting to win over $30,000. Things do not go to plan.<br /><br />Pozzi and Nashe are two very different individuals. Here are a couple of examples of the author’s writing style:<br />‘Once a man begins to recognise himself in another, he can no longer look on that person as a stranger.’<br />‘It was a dizzying prospect- to imagine all that freedom, to understand how little it mattered what choice he made.’<br /><br />Auster fans should find this an entertaining reading experience.<br />This book was first published in 1990.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12371236952388344909" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


